This bug is a tracing infrastructure correctness issue — `trace_cpu_idle()` was being called with RCU disabled in arch-specific idle implementations. The fix moves the trace calls to the generic code outside the RCU-disabled region. This doesn't affect scheduler behavior or task placement — it's purely about trace event safety. It cannot be observed through kSTEP's interfaces.

